article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 71, San Diego 62
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Josh Alexander scored a game-high 18 points to lead Stephen F. Austin to a 71-62 win over San Diego on Saturday in the season opener for both teams. Alexander hit 3-of-5 from beyond the 3-point arc. Chaz Dykes scored 15 points, and Antuane Miller and Matt Kingsley added 11 points each for the Lumberjacks. Brandon Johnson led San Diego with 18 points on 5-of-9 shooting. He hit 8-of-9 shots from the foul line, where San Diego was 21-of-26 overall. The Toreros shot just 1-of-13 from beyond the 3-point line. The Lumberjacks 35-28 at halftime.
